CIT on R501 road to Carltonville. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police have arrested 13 people, including a policeman and a soldier, following a cash-in-transit heist in Westonaria on Friday. The suspects were arrested in Carletonville near Krugersdorp. Those arrested include an SANDF member and a police officer. READ: CIT Heists: Crime Intelligence Unit activated Police say the SANDF member is out on a bail on a similar matter. There’s been a spike in cash in transit heists with over 50 cases since the start of the year with Gauteng as the hotspot. Police are hoping to link the suspects to other cash-in-transit heists in the province.